HEADWORD: house-raising
<hw>house-raising</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A gathering for the
construction of a house by a group of neighbors, usually in a rural
community, and sometimes accomplished in a single day; similar to a
<contr>barn-raising</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

